[1] Latvia, Poland
Date: 30 Nov 2012
Source: DEFRA, International disease monitoring/Preliminary outbreak assessments, Reference: VITT/1200 BTV in Eastern Europe 2012 [edited]
http://www.defra.gov.uk/animal-diseases/files/poa-btv14-20121130.pdf


Vaccine strain BTV-14 in Latvia and Poland: Update Outbreak Assessment
-----------------------------------------------
1. Disease Report
An update to the EU Reference Laboratory (EURL) for BTV at the Pirbright Institute has confirmed the samples from Poland have 100 percent sequence similarity to a South African vaccine strain of BTV-14. In addition, the National Reference Laboratory in Latvia has similarly confirmed strong similarity to the South African reference strain. Further samples have been sent to the EURL. In addition, the report notes that these samples are also similar to partial sequences from samples from Russia and Spain in 2011. Clinical disease has not been reported associated with these cases.

2. Situation Assessment
These data collectively suggest the release of the BTV-14 reference or vaccine strain into the field, possibly indicating the use of a live BTV-14 vaccine. The similarities of these different samples (Russia 2011, Spain 2011, Poland 2012 and Latvia 2012) indicate that they are derived from a common source and suggest significant spread of the virus in the field.

It will be important to determine whether vectors are responsible for the spread or whether there is wider use of the live vaccine.

We should remind livestock keepers that the use of live attenuated BTV vaccines is not authorised in the EU.

3. Conclusions
Several of these East European countries are likely to be entering the vector-free period, and, therefore, the risk of spread is reduced; nevertheless a new serotype through the possible use of live vaccine entering the EU even with few clinical signs is always a concern.

4. Authors
Dr Helen Roberts

5. References
1. All Commission Legislation is available from the Commission website http://eur-lex.europa.eu/RECH_mot.do.
2. European Commission (2012). Bluetongue Fax 06/2012; Update from Latvia regarding bluetongue vaccine like findings. Received 30 Nov 2012.
3. European Commission (2012). Bluetongue Fax 07/11/2012; Results from EU Reference Laboratory Bluetongue: vaccine-like strain. Received 30 Nov 2012.

